      "writtenOn": "2019-06-17T14:20:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just for the sake of going through the math:\n* we have a \"circle\" which is (for example) r by (r+e) in dimensions\n* in the worst case we (for example) non-uniformly scale the circle by a matrix s in x and (s+e) in y. \n* so the final scale for y is (r+e)*(s+e) \u003d s*r + e(s+r) + e^2\n* e \u003d\u003d 2^-12, so s+r would have to be \u003e 2^12 to see a radial difference of one pixel or greater. I don\u0027t know if you\u0027d even see a difference at that size.\n\nBut that said, I think it\u0027s reasonable to expect the client to give us equal radii if they want the fast path. It\u0027s a faster check as well.",
      "parentUuid": "2dacec2d_93a2a8f6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1261,
        "startChar": 8,
